Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
analyze_paths_by_bottleneck(25.10)          analyze_paths_by_bottleneck(25.10)

Name
       analyze_paths_by_bottleneck  - Creates categories according to the bot-
       tleneck analysis of the critical paths and fixes the violation  accord-
       ing to the bottleneck information

Syntax
        analyze_paths_by_bottleneck

       [-help]

       {-category <n> | -incr_delay {worst|total}}

       [-path_num <m>]

       [-max_slack <float>]

       [-min_slack <float>]

       [-master <master_category_name>]

       Creates categories according to the bottleneck analysis of the critical
       paths  and fixes the violation according to the bottleneck information.
       Bottleneck Analysis detects the instances that are  often  involved  in
       the  critical  paths  in the design. Any change in timing for these in-
       stances impacts multiple critical paths in the  design.  Therefore  you
       can  use  this information to change your design (floorplan, placement,
       constraints etc.) around these instances. The bottleneck analysis  com-
       putes  the  number of occurrences that an instance appears in the paths
       that you display in the Timing Debug window, and provides the following
       output:

              * Colors most used instance based on number of occurrences.

              * Creates <n> number of path categories for the  instances  with
                the highest number of occurrences. <n> is the number you spec-
                ify using the -category parameter.

       Users  can also perform bottleneck analysis of the critical paths based
       on incremental delay. Categories will be created based on the worst <m>
       paths with:

              * The biggest worst incr_delay contribution

              * The biggest total incr_delay contribution

       The command can be applied wherever the user loads the machine readable
       timing report. To delete the path categories created by  this  command,
       use delete_path_category.

       For  more  information  on creating path categories, see "Creating Path
       Categories" in the Debugging Timing Results chapter of User Guide.

       Note: The categories created by analyze_paths_by_bottleneck  cannot  be
       saved using the save_path_categories command. Additionally, the related
       sub-categories will not be saved.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each analyze_paths_by_bottleneck parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and  all  its  parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man analyze_paths_by_bottleneck

       -category <n>
              Specifies the number of categories to be created for most occur-
              ring instances.

       -incr_delay {worst|total}
              Specifies  that  the  categories  are  created  based  on  worst
              incr_delay contribution or total incr_delay contribution.

       -master <master_category_name>
              Specifies that the analysis should be  performed  only  for  the
              specified master category.

       -max_slack <float>
              Specifies  the max slack value of the critical paths for bottle-
              neck analysis based on incr_delay.

       -min_slack <float>
              Specifies the min slack value of the critical paths for  bottle-
              neck analysis based on incr_delay.

       -path_num <m>
              Specifies  the number of critical paths to be analyzed when per-
              forming bottleneck analysis based on incr_delay.

Examples
              * The following command creates path categories based on bottle-
                neck analysis of the critical paths on the instances:

                analyze_paths_by_bottleneck -category 2

                The  following  categories  are  created:  BOT_instance1   and
                BOT_instance2. You can change the number of categories.

              * The following command creates path categories based on bottle-
                neck  analysis  of the critical 20 paths on the worst incr_de-
                lay:

                analyze_paths_by_bottleneck -path_num 20 -incr_delay worst

                The following category is created: BOT_SI_WORST.

Related Information
       The Timing Budgeting chapter of the Innovus User Guide document.

